reviewText: These tiny creatures lead an amazing life. Much like bees they help pollinate our many plants and flowers. The metabolism, heart beat and wing flap rate are amazing numbers. Not only do these tiny creatures bring us joy and amazement, they also play a vital role in our ecosystem.

If you like this or not will depend somewhat on why you are watching it. Some documentaries are really for entertainment. This one is really for education. I watched it because we recently put bird feeders in the back yard, among them was a humming bird feeder. The humming birds stopped showing up and I thought perhaps this was because they were seasonal. Sure enough this show confirmed that and educated me on what time of year to put the feeder back out. We'll focus on the finches for now and when they humming birds migrate we'll put the food out for them. If you are really looking to learn a nice basic lesson on these birds, especially for those who plan on feeding them, this is the show to watch.

Fantastic video!  If you want to learn about hummingbirds of North America, this video is packed with tons of information in easy to understand language.  The video covers plants for hummingbirds, feeders, migration, behavior, etc.  The best thing about this video is that it features Sheri Williamson, who many consider to be THE hummingbird expert in the US.  If it comes from Sheri, it is factual and you can take it to the bank.
Saw it on TV and had to buy it.  I consider this a keeper DVD....

Hummingbirds of the backyard. I'm ten years old. Hummingbirds are my favorite birds and I want to know everything about them. This movie tells me almost everything about them. This movie does make attracting hummingbirds easy & fun! She tells you;
About the hummingbird migrating route,
How long it takes them to migrate,
About hummingbird feeders,
About the hummingbirds,
The names of the hummingbirds,
And much more! + the video is only 25 minutes, but it says fifty because they repeat the video and the second time there is no talking, just piano music. This is a great video. If you love hummingbirds, then you have to watch this 50 minute video!

The actual hummingbird content was great, but it seemed much more about the couple who discovered their migration habits. Good story, but we're more interested in the birds.  Film quality seemed a little amateurish, but I'm spoiled by Planet Earth and similar productions.

Very nice book.  I haven't gone through the entire book yet, but so far,  I'm impressed.  It has a lot of detailed facts and nice color photos. The book is great for anyone  interested in hummingbirds or maybe to promote interest  for someone who isn't very familiar with these miraculous little creatures.  I feed approximately 15 birds daily, and I've already learned more about  their  lives and habits.  I highly recommend  this book.  Just a note :  NEVER put red food coloring in home made sugar water.  : )
Hoped to see more birds, less talk.
